In re FIRST NAT. BANK OF YOUNGSTOWN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. May 15, 1902.) No. 1,042. Petition to Review an Order of the District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Ohio. Arrel, McVey & Robinson, for petitioner. Frank L. Baldwin, for bankrupt.

Before LURTON, DAY, and SEVERENS, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Affirmed, with costs.
